From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Randomize font enumeration order and pad visible count

Detection vector: Font fingerprinting measures the available fonts by
rendering text with each candidate font family and measuring the glyph
dimensions. The set of installed fonts uniquely identifies a device.
The enumeration order and count are additional entropy sources.

This patch shuffles the font list order per browser launch and pads
the visible count to a common baseline, reducing the uniqueness of
font-based fingerprints.

Surface: fonts
Closes: font enumeration fingerprinting

--- a/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/fonts/font_cache.cc
+++ b/third_party/blink/renderer/platform/fonts/font_cache.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ void FontCache::Init() {
+  // AgenticBrowser: shuffle the font family list using the launch seed.
+  // The seed is set via --ab-font-seed=<uint32>. Shuffling changes the
+  // enumeration order without hiding fonts, so pages that rely on specific
+  // fonts still render correctly.
+  ShuffleFontList(ab_font_seed_);
